If you had a spell with the name &quot;Vocerate Fire&quot; on it, and it was truly a Water pet.. would you call it a fire pet? Or a Water pet? Well.. that's a simple technicality. I suppose you'd call it a Fire pet based on the name. I'd call it a water pet based on the actual effect and reality of what the spell does. Do you see my point?<br>
<br>
The point stands, that the Necro Epic is the only spell that has an under 50th level effect. That's all. <br>
<br>
It's great that it's Mana Free... but being mana free and clickable isn't the end all be all of items. And with the higher casting time, as far as the spell goes.. it's a downgrade because most Necros STILL have to have a real Snare memmed in a spell slot and it can't be used in many situations where casting time is important. 1 resist and you might as well zone. It's an upgrade because of the stats on the weapon and the fact that it's mana free. Epic's should be SOLEY an upgrade. In every way. That's what in my opinion makes them &quot;Epic&quot;<br>
<br>
I truly am sorry for being short on patience with you. I'm a hot tempered guy who didn't have his wife there at the time to speak calming words like &quot;If you post that you are just gonna look like a jackass!&quot;... I'm a work in progress <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
